<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Select on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/select/</link><description>Recent content in Select on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><atom:link href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/select/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>[Solution] Bash Select Syntax Error</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/bash/bash-select-error/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/bash/bash-select-error/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="bash-select-syntax-error-fix"&gt;Bash Select Syntax Error Fix&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Select syntax errors occur when the &lt;code&gt;select&lt;/code&gt; loop has incorrect syntax, is used non-interactively, or has mismatched &lt;code&gt;do&lt;/code&gt;/&lt;code&gt;done&lt;/code&gt; blocks.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="what-this-error-means"&gt;What This Error Means&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The &lt;code&gt;select&lt;/code&gt; statement creates a numbered menu from a list and reads user input. It requires an interactive shell or proper stdin redirection. Errors indicate syntax problems or non-interactive usage.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Used in non-interactive shell (piped or redirected input)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Missing &lt;code&gt;in&lt;/code&gt; keyword&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Missing &lt;code&gt;do&lt;/code&gt;/&lt;code&gt;done&lt;/code&gt; block&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;PS3 prompt not set&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Missing &lt;code&gt;esac&lt;/code&gt; or &lt;code&gt;done&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="1-ensure-correct-syntax"&gt;1. Ensure correct syntax&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# RIGHT:&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;PS3&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Select option: &amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;select&lt;/span&gt; opt in &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Start&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Stop&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Quit&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;do&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;case&lt;/span&gt; $opt in
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; Start&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; echo &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Starting&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; ;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; Stop&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; echo &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Stopping&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; ;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; Quit&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; break ;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; *&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; echo &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Invalid option&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; ;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;esac&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;done&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="2-set-ps3-before-select"&gt;2. Set PS3 before select&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;PS3&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Choose: &amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Must be set before select&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;select&lt;/span&gt; item in apple banana cherry; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;do&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; echo &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;You chose: &lt;/span&gt;$item&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; break
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;done&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="3-use-with-proper-shell"&gt;3. Use with proper shell&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;#!/bin/bash # select is a bash feature, not sh
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;PS3&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Pick one: &amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;select&lt;/span&gt; choice in A B C; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;do&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; echo &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;$choice&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; break
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;done&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="bash-case-error"&gt;Case Error&lt;/a&gt; — case statement syntax&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="bash-while-error"&gt;While Error&lt;/a&gt; — loop syntax issues&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Bash Select: Not Found in List Error Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/bash/bash-select-menu-error/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/bash/bash-select-menu-error/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="bash-select-not-found-in-list-error-fix"&gt;Bash Select: Not Found in List Error Fix&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A bash select error occurs when the &lt;code&gt;select&lt;/code&gt; command is used with an empty list or when the user enters a value not in the list.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="what-this-error-means"&gt;What This Error Means&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The &lt;code&gt;select&lt;/code&gt; command in bash generates a numbered menu from a list and prompts the user to choose. If the list is empty, no menu is displayed. If &lt;code&gt;REPLY&lt;/code&gt; is not in range, &lt;code&gt;$REPLY&lt;/code&gt; contains an empty value.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] SQL GROUP BY Error Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/sql/sql-group-by-error/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/sql/sql-group-by-error/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;This error occurs when a SELECT statement includes a column that is neither aggregated nor included in the GROUP BY clause. The message reads: &lt;code&gt;Expression not in GROUP BY clause&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="what-this-error-means"&gt;What This Error Means&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;When using GROUP BY, every non-aggregated column in SELECT must appear in the GROUP BY clause. MySQL&amp;rsquo;s &lt;code&gt;ONLY_FULL_GROUP_BY&lt;/code&gt; mode enforces this ANSI SQL standard.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;SELECT includes columns not in GROUP BY or aggregate function&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Using &lt;code&gt;SELECT *&lt;/code&gt; with GROUP BY&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Missing GROUP BY for aggregate queries&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Using &lt;code&gt;sql_mode=ONLY_FULL_GROUP_BY&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="fix-1-add-all-non-aggregated-columns-to-group-by"&gt;Fix 1: Add all non-aggregated columns to GROUP BY&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-sql" data-lang="sql"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;-- Wrong
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;SELECT&lt;/span&gt; department, name, &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;COUNT&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;FROM&lt;/span&gt; employees
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;GROUP&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;BY&lt;/span&gt; department;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;-- Correct
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;SELECT&lt;/span&gt; department, name, &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;COUNT&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;FROM&lt;/span&gt; employees
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;GROUP&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;BY&lt;/span&gt; department, name;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-2-use-aggregate-functions"&gt;Fix 2: Use aggregate functions&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-sql" data-lang="sql"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;-- Get one name per department
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;SELECT&lt;/span&gt; department, &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;MAX&lt;/span&gt;(name) &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;AS&lt;/span&gt; sample_name, &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;COUNT&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;FROM&lt;/span&gt; employees
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;GROUP&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;BY&lt;/span&gt; department;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-3-use-any_value-for-non-deterministic-columns"&gt;Fix 3: Use ANY_VALUE for non-deterministic columns&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-sql" data-lang="sql"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;SELECT&lt;/span&gt; department, ANY_VALUE(name), &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;COUNT&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;FROM&lt;/span&gt; employees
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;GROUP&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;BY&lt;/span&gt; department;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="examples"&gt;Examples&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-sql" data-lang="sql"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;SELECT&lt;/span&gt; user_id, created_at, &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;COUNT&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;FROM&lt;/span&gt; orders
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;GROUP&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;BY&lt;/span&gt; user_id;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;-- ERROR 1055: Expression not in GROUP BY clause
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="no-grouping.md"&gt;No GROUP BY Expression&lt;/a&gt; — related GROUP BY issue&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="sql-unknown-column-orderby.md"&gt;Unknown Column in ORDER BY&lt;/a&gt; — ORDER BY references non-grouped column&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] SQL Unknown Column in ORDER BY Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/sql/sql-unknown-column-orderby/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/sql/sql-unknown-column-orderby/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;This error occurs when the ORDER BY clause references a column that does not exist or is not available in the current query context.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="what-this-error-means"&gt;What This Error Means&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The database cannot find the column specified in the ORDER BY clause. This can happen when the column doesn&amp;rsquo;t exist, or when using GROUP BY and the column is not in SELECT or GROUP BY.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Column name misspelled in ORDER BY&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Column not in SELECT list when using ONLY_FULL_GROUP_BY&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ordering by alias that wasn&amp;rsquo;t defined&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Column from a table not in the FROM clause&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="fix-1-verify-the-column-exists"&gt;Fix 1: Verify the column exists&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-sql" data-lang="sql"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;-- Check available columns
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;SHOW&lt;/span&gt; COLUMNS &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;FROM&lt;/span&gt; orders;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;-- Use correct column name
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;SELECT&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;FROM&lt;/span&gt; orders &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;ORDER&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;BY&lt;/span&gt; created_at &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;DESC&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-2-order-by-column-alias"&gt;Fix 2: Order by column alias&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-sql" data-lang="sql"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;SELECT&lt;/span&gt; name, price &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt; quantity &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;AS&lt;/span&gt; total
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;FROM&lt;/span&gt; order_items
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;ORDER&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;BY&lt;/span&gt; total &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;DESC&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-3-order-by-column-position"&gt;Fix 3: Order by column position&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-sql" data-lang="sql"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;SELECT&lt;/span&gt; name, price, quantity
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;FROM&lt;/span&gt; order_items
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;ORDER&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;BY&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;3&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;DESC&lt;/span&gt;; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;-- orders by the 3rd column (quantity)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="examples"&gt;Examples&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-sql" data-lang="sql"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;SELECT&lt;/span&gt; id, name &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;FROM&lt;/span&gt; users &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;ORDER&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;BY&lt;/span&gt; email;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;-- ERROR 1054: Unknown column &amp;#39;email&amp;#39; in &amp;#39;order clause&amp;#39;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="column-not-found.md"&gt;Column Not Found&lt;/a&gt; — column doesn&amp;rsquo;t exist&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="group-by-error.md"&gt;GROUP BY Error&lt;/a&gt; — GROUP BY related issue&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item><item><title>Oracle View Error</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tools/oracle/oracle-view-error/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tools/oracle/oracle-view-error/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="oracle-view-error"&gt;Oracle View Error&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An Oracle view error occurs when a view fails to compile or returns errors during querying. Views are stored SELECT statements that act as virtual tables.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Base table does not exist or has been dropped&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Column references in view are invalid&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Insufficient privileges on base tables&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;View contains syntax errors&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="check-view-status"&gt;Check View Status&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-sql" data-lang="sql"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;SELECT&lt;/span&gt; object_name, status &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;FROM&lt;/span&gt; user_objects &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;WHERE&lt;/span&gt; object_type &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;VIEW&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="compile-view"&gt;Compile View&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-sql" data-lang="sql"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;ALTER&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;VIEW&lt;/span&gt; myview COMPILE;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="check-view-definition"&gt;Check View Definition&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-sql" data-lang="sql"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;SELECT&lt;/span&gt; text &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;FROM&lt;/span&gt; user_views &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;WHERE&lt;/span&gt; view_name &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;MYVIEW&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="check-compilation-errors"&gt;Check Compilation Errors&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-sql" data-lang="sql"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;SHOW&lt;/span&gt; ERRORS &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;VIEW&lt;/span&gt; myview;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="recreate-view"&gt;Recreate View&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-sql" data-lang="sql"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;CREATE&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;OR&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;REPLACE&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;VIEW&lt;/span&gt; myview &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;AS&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;SELECT&lt;/span&gt; id, name &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;FROM&lt;/span&gt; users &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;WHERE&lt;/span&gt; active &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="check-dependencies"&gt;Check Dependencies&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-sql" data-lang="sql"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;SELECT&lt;/span&gt; referenced_name, referenced_type
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;FROM&lt;/span&gt; user_dependencies
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;WHERE&lt;/span&gt; name &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;MYVIEW&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="grant-view-permissions"&gt;Grant View Permissions&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-sql" data-lang="sql"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;GRANT&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;SELECT&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;ON&lt;/span&gt; myview &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;TO&lt;/span&gt; another_user;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="examples"&gt;Examples&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-sql" data-lang="sql"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;CREATE&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;VIEW&lt;/span&gt; active_users &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;AS&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;SELECT&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;FROM&lt;/span&gt; users &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;WHERE&lt;/span&gt; active &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;-- View created
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;DROP&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;TABLE&lt;/span&gt; users;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;-- View becomes INVALID
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;ALTER&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;VIEW&lt;/span&gt; active_users COMPILE;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;-- ORA-00942: table or view does not exist
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tools/oracle/oracle-trigger-error/"&gt;Trigger Error&lt;/a&gt; — trigger issues&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=""&gt;Synonym Error&lt;/a&gt; — synonym issues&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] C errno 115 EINPROGRESS — Operation in Progress Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/errno-115/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/errno-115/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="solution-c-errno-115-einprogress--operation-in-progress-fix"&gt;[Solution] C errno 115 EINPROGRESS — Operation in Progress Fix&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;When you call &lt;code&gt;connect()&lt;/code&gt; on a non-blocking socket, the connection cannot complete immediately. Instead of blocking, the kernel starts the connection in the background and returns &lt;code&gt;-1&lt;/code&gt; with &lt;code&gt;errno&lt;/code&gt; set to &lt;code&gt;EINPROGRESS&lt;/code&gt; (110 on Linux). This is not an error — it is the expected behavior for non-blocking I/O. You must use &lt;code&gt;select()&lt;/code&gt;, &lt;code&gt;poll()&lt;/code&gt;, or &lt;code&gt;epoll()&lt;/code&gt; to wait for the socket to become writable, then check the connection result with &lt;code&gt;getsockopt(SO_ERROR)&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Ruby IO::WaitReadable — Non-Blocking Read Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/ruby/io-wait-error/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/ruby/io-wait-error/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="iowaitreadable--non-blocking-read-fix"&gt;IO::WaitReadable — Non-Blocking Read Fix&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An &lt;code&gt;IO::WaitReadable&lt;/code&gt; is raised when a non-blocking read operation would block because no data is currently available.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="description"&gt;Description&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;IO::WaitReadable&lt;/code&gt; (also &lt;code&gt;IO::EAGAINWaitReadable&lt;/code&gt;) is raised by non-blocking I/O operations when no data is available to read. This is common with non-blocking sockets and pipes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Common scenarios:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Non-blocking socket read&lt;/strong&gt; — no data available yet.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Non-blocking pipe read&lt;/strong&gt; — writer hasn&amp;rsquo;t sent data.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;EAGAIN/EWOULDBLOCK&lt;/strong&gt; — system resource temporarily unavailable.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;IO.select timeout&lt;/strong&gt; — no descriptors ready within timeout.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-ruby" data-lang="ruby"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Cause 1: Non-blocking read without data available&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;socket &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;TCPSocket&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;new(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;example.com&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;80&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;socket&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;read_nonblock(&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1024&lt;/span&gt;) &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# IO::WaitReadable if no data ready&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Cause 2: Using IO.select with timeout&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;ready &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;IO&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;select(&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;[&lt;/span&gt;socket&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;]&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;[]&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;[]&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;) &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# 1 second timeout&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;ready &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# nil if timeout expires&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Cause 3: Non-blocking gets&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;$stdin&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;read_nonblock(&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1024&lt;/span&gt;) &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# IO::WaitReadable&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Cause 4: Pipe read without writer&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;reader, writer &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;IO&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;pipe
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;reader&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;read_nonblock(&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1024&lt;/span&gt;) &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# IO::WaitReadable&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="solutions"&gt;Solutions&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="fix-1-use-ioselect-to-wait-for-readiness"&gt;Fix 1: Use IO.select to wait for readiness&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-ruby" data-lang="ruby"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Wrong — may raise IO::WaitReadable&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;socket &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;TCPSocket&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;new(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;example.com&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;80&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;data &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; socket&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;read_nonblock(&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1024&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Correct — wait for socket to be readable&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;socket &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;TCPSocket&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;new(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;example.com&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;80&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;ready &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;IO&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;select(&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;[&lt;/span&gt;socket&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;]&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;[]&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;[]&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;5&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; ready
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; data &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; socket&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;read_nonblock(&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1024&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;else&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; puts &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Read timed out&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;end&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-2-rescue-iowaitreadable"&gt;Fix 2: Rescue IO::WaitReadable&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-ruby" data-lang="ruby"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;begin&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; data &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; socket&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;read_nonblock(&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1024&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;rescue&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;IO&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;WaitReadable&lt;/span&gt;
